The paper deals with the problem of out-of-distribution detection in machine learning models, specifically in convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), software engineering (cs.SD), and multimedia (cs.MM). Given that the paper focuses on image and audio benchmarks, it is most likely to belong to the first three categories, with cs.LG being the most likely. However, since the paper also proposes novel metrics for characterizing OOD sets, it could also be relevant to the other two categories.
